│ which are the scalar instructions at the root of the vectorization tree. The size of `Scalars` is `Graph[0].size()`.                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The problem seems to be that `Graph[0]` can have fewer elements than the vector width (`VF.getKnownVectorWidth()`), especially if some lanes are undef. In this case, `Scalars` will be  │
│ smaller than the vector width. However, the `ShuffleMask` is created with a size equal to the vector width, and its elements can be indices up to `vector width - 1`. When               │
│ `reorderScalars` is called, `Mask[i]` (which comes from `ShuffleMask`) can be an index larger than `Scalars.size() - 1`, leading to the crash.                                           │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ A simple fix is to ensure that `reorderScalars` is only called when the number of scalars is equal to the vector width. If they are not equal, it means some lanes are undef, and        │
│ reordering is not safe with the current mask generation logic. This can be achieved by adding a check before the call to `reorderScalars`.                                               │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ // In BoUpSLP::reorderBottomToTop                                                                                                                                                        │
│ // ...                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ if (!IgnoreReorder) {                                                                                                                                                                    │
│   // The shuffle mask is based on the vector width, but the number of scalars                                                                                                            │
│   // may be smaller. Only reorder if the sizes match.                                                                                                                                    │
│   if (Scalars.size() == VF.getKnownVectorWidth())                                                                                                                                        │
│     reorderScalars(Scalars, Mask);                                                                                                                                                       │
│ }                                                                                                                                                                                        │
│ // ...                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ This change is localized to `BoUpSLP::reorderBottomToTop` in `SLPVectorizer.cpp` and directly addresses the condition that leads to the out-of-bounds access.                            │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ I will now apply this change using `sed`.                                                                                                                                                │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i "s/reorderScalars(Scalars, Mask);/if (Scalars.size() == VF.getKnownVectorWidth()) reorderScalars(Scalars, Mask);/" llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
